PN,31611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780567570
OL,3,CFrom increased chance of heatwaves to
OL,4,Cmore rain: What does summer have in
OL,5,Cstore?
OL,7,FThe sunny skies and high temperatures
OL,8,Fcontinued through June, July and
OL,9,FAugust - and it was another record-
OL,10,Fbreaking summer for heat.
OL,12,FIt pushed 1976 out of the top 5
OL,13,Fhottest summers ever, which have all
OL,14,Foccurred since 2003.
OL,16,FThis year marks the 50th anniversary
OL,17,Fof the record-breaking summer of 1976.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31612
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1780567570
OL,3,CFrom increased chance of heatwaves to
OL,4,Cmore rain: What does summer have in
OL,5,Cstore?
OL,7,FIt remains a unique summer, having
OL,8,Frecorded 16 days above 32C - and
OL,9,Fdespite our recent higher temperatures
OL,10,F- we've never seen a heatwave with
OL,11,Fsuch longevity since.
OL,13,FRecent hot summers differ from the one
OL,14,Fexperienced in 1976 as we see
OL,15,Fconsistently higher temperatures by
OL,16,Fday and night, as well as warmer sea
OL,17,Ftemperatures.
OL,19,FThat has given an overall higher mean
OL,20,F- or average - temperature in recent
OL,21,Fyears.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
